# MOC - How I Turn Scattered Ideas into Finished Writing

## Foundation: The Thinking System
- [[zettelkasten-as-thinking-system]] - Luhmann's method: one idea per note, linked, structure emerges
- [[one-idea-per-note]] - the atomic unit, the constraint that makes it work
- [[links-do-the-work]] - each link forces you to articulate a relationship
- [[compound-interest-on-thinking]] - today's half-formed thought becomes next month's breakthrough

## The Workflow Phases
- [[think-alone-first]] - resist AI here, this is raw human thinking
- [[the-blue-lagoon-analogy]] - the thinking is geothermal, AI is infrastructure, output is the lagoon
- [[ai-as-infrastructure-for-thinking]] - AI walks the chain, surfaces what you missed
- [[the-ai-surfaces-connections-you-missed]] - the network gets richer through collaboration
- [[the-bullet-draft-method]] - AI sequences the network into a story arc
- [[the-two-paths-converge]] - write yourself or draft with AI: both end the same way
- [[the-writing-is-a-byproduct]] - the thinking was already done in the links

## Core Principles
- [[ai-expands-not-compresses]] - the whole piece hinges on this distinction
- [[ai-value-is-in-the-process]] - why the output isn't the point
- [[ai-outputs-are-inputs]] - separation of AI contribution from your own, built into the structure
- [[firewall-your-thinking]] - physically separate your ideas from external inputs
- [[authorship-lives-in-judgement]] - could you defend this in conversation? That's the test
- [[echo-chamber-steering]] - actively steer AI toward challenge, not confirmation
- [[deliberate-incompleteness]] - park half-formed thoughts, let the links hold context

## The Collaboration Model
- [[ai-as-co-thinker]] - level two: stateless pressure testing
- [[ai-as-persistent-collaborator]] - level three: contextual, cumulative
- [[ai-makes-thinking-harder-not-easier]] - more demanding, not less
- [[markdown-as-universal-format]] - the file format that makes it all portable

